import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_json('cars.json')

# Plot histogram of car prices
sns.histplot(data=data, x='price', kde=True, color='blue')
plt.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median price: ${:.2f}'.format(data['price'].median()))
plt.legend()
plt.title('What is the distribution of car prices?')
plt.xlabel('Price')
plt.ylabel('Frequency')

plt.show()
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_json('cars.json')

# Create scatter plot
sns.scatterplot(x='horsepower', y='price', data=data)

# Set chart title
plt.title('What is the relationship between car price and horsepower?', wrap=True)

# Add legend with single value
plt.axvline(x=data['horsepower'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Median horsepower: {:.2f}'.format(data['horsepower'].median()))

# Add legend
plt.legend()

# Show plot
plt.show()
```
